item.title: [HIVE-19968] UDF exception is not throw out
item.description:
udf init failed, and throw a exception, but hive catch it and do nothing, leading to app succ, but no data is generated.

GenericUDFReflect.java#evaluate()

try {  

   o = null;  

   o = ReflectionUtils.newInstance(c, null);

}   catch (Exception e) {  

// ignored

}

ATTACHMENT ID: 12951643 - PreCommit-HIVE-Build

interesting that it was always 568

"reflect("java.lang.Integer", "valueOf", key, 16)" throwed exception because of Integer instantiation?
valueOf is a static method - I think static methods should work without instance

yes, it threw the exception because of instantiation

I have to review this as the current implementation supports static methods: if the instantiation fails, it goes forward, and tries to find method, calls it, and method.invoke(obj, params) works without an instance, obj can even be null, it's ignored anyway.

it would be suitable to catch NoSuchMethodException separately on instantiation and ignore (it could be okay if the class hasn't got a default or parameterless constructor), but throw all other exceptions forward
